milestones.description: Alec Stewart has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (126) for ENG, going past Graham Gooch
This is the highest match aggregate (417) involving teams England & Zimbabwe in ODIs
Guy Whittall has broken the record for most catches in an innings (4) in ODIs for ZIM, going past Campbell's 3

stories.title: 2nd Match, NatWest Series, Eng v Zim, Statistical Highlights
stories.summary: It was the 1607th ODI in cricket history

stories.title: Zimbabwe's clear-cut victory
stories.summary:
NatWest Series, The Oval: England (207 all out off 50 overs) lost to
Zimbabwe (210 for five off 48.2 overs) by five wickets

stories.title: Zimbabwe maintain winning momentum
stories.summary:
Zimbabwe's resilience showed through the Kennington gloom as they fought back
from a position of almost despair to beat England by five wickets in the NatWest Series limited-overs match at The Oval to move comfortably to the top of the triangular

stories.title: Zimbabwe resistance flowers in poor light
stories.summary:
After losing three wickets, one of them controversially, for 35 runs in
pursuit of England's total of 207, Zimbabwe appeared to be as good as
buried

stories.title: Strang brings Zimbabwe back into game
stories.summary:
A combination of the second break for rain and the rejuvenated leg-spin of
Paul Strang turned the England innings on its head when the team had built
such a fine foundation to their innings

stories.title: Debutant Trescothick gives England cracking start
stories.summary:
The left-handed debutant Trescothick played a most impressive innings
of 79 as England ran to 150 for three at a scoring rate of almost five an
over against Zimbabwe in their NatWest Series match against Zimbabwe at The
Oval

stories.title: High scores in prospect
stories.summary:
On an overcast morning, England won the toss in the second match of the
triangular NatWest Series and decided to bat
